USP
Originally designed for the American market, the USP (Universal Self-loading Pistol) has found international acceptance as an accurate and ultra-reliable handgun. Features favored by U.S. law enforcement and military users provided much of the design criteria for the USP. The controls are uniquely American, influenced by such famous designs as the Government Model 1911 pistol.

All USPs use a fiber-reinforced polymer frame stiffened by stainless steel inserts at areas subject to stress and friction. HK pioneered this use of polymer materials in the production of handguns more than 30 years ago with the development of the VP70Z and P9S pistols.

The USP control lever, a combination safety and decocking lever, is frame mounted and quickly accessible, unlike the slide-mounted safeties common on many semi-automatic pistols.

Using a modified Browning-type action with a special patented recoil reduction system, the USP recoil reduction system reduces recoil effects on pistol components and also lowers the recoil forces felt by the shooter. This same recoil reduction system has been tested and proven in the HK Mark 23 pistol developed for the U.S. Special Operations Command. The USP recoil reduction system is insensitive to ammunition types and requires no special adjustment or maintenance. It functions effectively in all USP models.

The modular design of the USP's internal components allows the control lever function to be switched from the left to the right side of the pistol for left-handed shooters. The USP can also be converted from one type of trigger firing mode to another. This includes combination double-action and single-action (DA/SA) modes and double action only (DAO) modes.

The USP is available in nine trigger/firing mode configurations and three calibers. 9mm, .40 S&W and .45 ACP.

Corrosion proof fiber-reinforced polymer frame

postcontent:
NFA REVOCABLE LIVING TRUST

What this Trust does: It allows you to obtain an NFA item easily and without CLEO approval, fingerprints, etc.  Also, my Trust is designed to keep your Schedule A confidential unless required by the BATF by using an Assignment of Property.

As a Texas lawyer, I cannot stress how critical it is that your NFA Trust is legal, proper, and air-tight.  I created this NFA Trust so that you will have all the documents you will need.  Did you know that if a person is NOT listed as a Trustee and handles/uses your NFA item, you could be charged with a serious Felony crime?  I include easy to fill out Assignment and Affidavit of Trustee.  Simply have your friend or family member fill one out and they can use the NFA item instantly!  No waiting, no need to file with the Court.  Then, they can resign as Trustee if you prefer to not keep them listed on your trust at ANY TIME!  

This can be a complex process and I am here to help.  Please feel free to contact me with any questions you may have.  I specialize in Estate Planning and Probate Law and I am a serious gun-enthusiast!  Let me put my knowledge and talents to work for you.  That includes drafting the entire Trust with your specifics, answering your questions, and customizing each document to your needs.

Did you know you can also put regular firearms and items into this Trust?  By getting an NFA Trust, you can obtain Title II weapons/items along with properly establishing  good Estate Planning for all your firearms.  


What the Trust includes:

- The NFA Revocable Trust with a Schedule A (16 pages)
- Certification of Trust (7 pages, this is the version you send in to the BATF with the required Forms)
- Assignment of Property (2 pages, send this in with your BATF forms)
- Affidavit of Trustee (1 page)
- Appointment of Trustee (1 Page)
- Trustee resignation (1 Page)
- Revocation/Modification of Trust (2 pages, if you want to revoke the Trust or modify the Trust, this form allows you to do so easily)

I look forward to helping you obtain your own NFA items and protecting your property while keeping your information and collection as private as possible.

title: For Sale:  Egyptian Rasheed Carbine 7.62x39 Semi-Auto - Excellent Condition
postcontent:
This is a Rasheed Carbine made in Egypt. The Rasheed is tough to find and records suggest that there were only 8000 of them ever produced making it one of the rarest of all military production rifles. Of that 8000, my research indicates that only about 2000 were imported into the US making them quite collectible. 

This Rasheed is in excellent overall condition with a bright & shiny bore. All of these rifles were issued, and most I've seen over the years were pretty beaten up from the service the saw in Egypt. So finding one in excellent condition like this one is no easy task.

The Rasheed design is a combination of the AG42B Ljungman from WWII and the more modern SKS. Like the SKS it's chambered in 7.62 x 39 and is loaded from the top using the same 10 round stripper clips. It is quite capable of a high sustained rate of semi-auto fire just like it's cousin - the SKS. This rifle comes with attached blade style bayonet, original sling, and 10 stripper clips.

Asking price is $950. FTF with pickup in Brandon. Must be 21 or older and a Florida resident to purchase.

title: For Sale:  Beware of scammers
postcontent:
Beware of scammers. If someone is in the same state as you and refuses to meet in person to exchange rifle for cash, they are a scammer. 
If the deal sounds too good it likely is.
I had 2 successful sales and I bought 1 item on here.
try to meet during daylight so you can inspect the item to see if condition is as described.

But 50% of all responses I have gotten from sellers here were obvious scammers.

If there are red flags during contact its likely a scam.
What are red flags?
- Not wanting to give out phone number
- Not wanting to meet in person if in same state
- Changing stories where they are located
